        "description": "<p><em>Lost World Pinball</em> is a dinosaur themed pinball game that consists of a single table. The game plays like other pinball games with two keys being used to control left and right flippers while a third has to be hold down to launch the ball. The player has three balls which has to be used to reach the highest score. The table consists of bumpers (10 points), red power strips (10 points), plungers (20 points) and red marks (30 points). Upon reaching 10,000 points an extra ball is given. Hitting all plungers lead to a 2x multiplier the first time and a 3x multiplier the second time.</p>\n<p>Next to the table is an animated picture of a volcano, a dinosaur and a prehistoric fly. It is possible to make the volcano erupt by having the dinosaur catch the fly with his tongue. The tongue grows larger when hitting red marks and for it to reach full length twelve hits are needed. When it erupts the playing ball disappears but will reappear ready to be launched again. The point values are then ten times their regular value.</p>",
