        "description": "<p><em>Micro Checkers</em> is a basic adaptation of the board game Checkers/Draughts. The game is for one player who competes against an AI opponent. Played on a 8 by 8 board, the player has orange checkers while the opponent's are green. To the right of the board is a prompt where the player enters commands to move pieces. This is done by entering the coordinates of the squares that the player wants to move between. After making jumps the player has to enter -1,-1 to end the move. The game follows the rules of the traditional board game and the player that first removes all pieces of the opponent wins.</p>",
